<body>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <div class="app-info">
                <p><strong>Skoll AI - Study Helper</strong></p>
                <p>Developed by PrepMaster AI (com.prepmasterai.app)</p>
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="section">
            <p>This Privacy Policy describes how Skoll AI - Study Helper ("we", "our", or "the App") collects, uses, and protects your information when you use our mobile application. Skoll AI is developed and maintained by PrepMaster AI.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="highlight-box">
            <strong>Your Privacy Matters:</strong> We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring transparency about how we handle your data.
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
            
            <h3>1.1 Personal Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> When you sign in with Google, we collect your name, email address, and profile picture through Google Sign-In services</li>
                <li><strong>User-Generated Content:</strong> Study materials, notes, and academic content you create or upload within the app</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>1.2 Camera and Image Data</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Camera Access:</strong> We request camera permission to capture study materials, textbooks, notes, and educational content</li>
                <li><strong>Image Processing:</strong> Images are processed using AI technology (Google Gemini API) to generate study aids, solve problems, and create flashcards</li>
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> Images are stored locally on your device and temporarily transmitted to our secure backend server for AI processing</li>
                <li><strong>Retention:</strong> Processed images are not permanently stored on our servers and are deleted after processing is complete</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>1.3 Technical Information</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system version, and app version</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> App usage patterns, feature interactions, and performance data collected through Firebase Analytics</li>
                <li><strong>Crash Reports:</strong> Error logs and crash data collected through Firebase Crashlytics to improve app stability</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>1.4 Advertising Data</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Ad Identifiers:</strong> Google Advertising ID for serving personalized advertisements through Google AdMob</li>
                <li><strong>Ad Interaction Data:</strong> Information about ads you view or interact with</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Core Functionality:</strong> To provide AI-powered study features including MCQ generation, math problem solving, flashcard creation, concept explanations, and handwriting digitization</li>
                <li><strong>User Authentication:</strong> To create and manage your account through Firebase Authentication and Google Sign-In</li>
                <li><strong>Image Processing:</strong> To analyze captured images and generate educational content using Google Gemini AI</li>
                <li><strong>App Improvement:</strong> To analyze app usage, identify bugs, and enhance user experience</li>
                <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> To display relevant advertisements through Google AdMob</li>
                <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To send important updates, notifications, or respond to your inquiries</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>3. Camera Permission Details</h2>
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h3>How We Use Camera Access:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Capture study materials, notes, and textbooks for AI analysis</li>
                    <li>Scan mathematical problems for step-by-step solutions</li>
                    <li>Photograph educational content for flashcard generation</li>
                    <li>Digitize handwritten notes</li>
                    <li>Create visual study aids</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Camera Data Protection:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Explicit Activation:</strong> Camera only activates when you explicitly use capture features</li>
                    <li><strong>No Background Access:</strong> We never access your camera in the background</li>
                    <li><strong>User Control:</strong> You maintain full control over which images to capture and process</li>
                    <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Images are primarily stored on your device</li>
                    <li><strong>Secure Transmission:</strong> When images are sent to our server for AI processing, they are transmitted securely via HTTPS</li>
                    <li><strong>Temporary Processing:</strong> Images are deleted from our servers immediately after AI processing is complete</li>
                    <li><strong>Permission Control:</strong> You can revoke camera permission at any time through your device settings</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>4. Third-Party Services and Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>We integrate the following third-party services that may collect and process your data:</p>
            
            <h3>4.1 Google Services</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Firebase (Google):</strong> Authentication, Analytics, and Crashlytics</li>
                <li><strong>Google Sign-In:</strong> For user authentication</li>
                <li><strong>Google AdMob:</strong> For displaying advertisements</li>
                <li><strong>Google Gemini API:</strong> For AI-powered image analysis and content generation</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4.2 Data Sharing</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>We share captured images with Google Gemini API solely for AI processing purposes</li>
                <li>We do not sell your personal information to third parties</li>
                <li>We may share anonymized, aggregated data for analytics purposes</li>
                <li>We may disclose information if required by law or to protect our rights</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Study materials and captured images are stored locally on your device using Room Database</li>
                <li><strong>Cloud Storage:</strong> Account information is stored securely on Firebase servers</li>
                <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Data transmitted between your device and our servers is encrypted using HTTPS/TLS</li>
                <li><strong>Security Measures:</strong> We implement industry-standard security practices to protect your data</li>
                <li><strong>Server Location:</strong> Our backend servers are hosted on Google Cloud Platform (europe-west1 region)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access and Control:</strong> You can access, modify, or delete your study materials within the app</li>
                <li><strong>Account Deletion:</strong> You can delete your account and associated data by contacting us</li>
                <li><strong>Camera Permission:</strong> You can revoke camera access at any time through your device settings (Settings > Apps > Skoll AI > Permissions)</li>
                <li><strong>Opt-Out of Personalized Ads:</strong> You can opt out of personalized advertising through your device's ad settings</li>
                <li><strong>Data Portability:</strong> You can request a copy of your data by contacting us</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>Skoll AI is designed for students of all ages. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Account information is retained as long as your account is active</li>
                <li>Study materials are stored locally on your device until you delete them</li>
                <li>Images sent for AI processing are deleted immediately after processing</li>
                <li>Analytics data is retained according to Firebase's data retention policies</li>
                <li>Upon account deletion, we will delete your personal information within 30 days</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
            <p>Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own, including the European Union (where our servers are located) and the United States (where some third-party services are based). We ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to protect your data in accordance with applicable laws.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any significant changes by:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Posting the new Privacy Policy in the app</li>
                <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date</li>
                <li>Sending you a notification (for material changes)</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Your continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>11. Third-Party Links</h2>
            <p>Our app may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
            <div class="contact-info">
                <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal data, please contact us at:</p>
                <p><strong>Email:</strong> support@prepmasterai.app</p>
                <p><strong>App Name:</strong> Skoll AI - Study Helper</p>
                <p><strong>Developer:</strong> PrepMaster AI</p>
                <p><strong>Package Name:</strong> com.prepmasterai.app</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>13. Legal Compliance</h2>
            <p>This Privacy Policy is designed to comply with:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Google Play Store Developer Distribution Agreement</li>
                <li>Google Play User Data Policy</li>
                <li>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) where applicable</li>
                <li>California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) where applicable</li>
                <li>Other applicable data protection laws</li>
